### ShopHub Backend API Tests
### Use this file with the REST Client extension to test your APIs

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health

### Example API calls (update these based on your actual endpoints)

### Get all products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Get product by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Create a new product
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Sample Product",
  "description": "This is a sample product",
  "price": 29.99,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

### Update a product
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Updated Product",
  "description": "This is an updated product",
  "price": 39.99,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

### Delete a product
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1

### Authentication endpoints (if you have them)

### Register user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Protected endpoint (add Authorization header after login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: {{contentType}}
